	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9924416222580><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=6140&mid=9924416222580>RE: Where you buy these</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=6140&mid=9924416222580#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=31407><span id=Sage>zhmoozo</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>182 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Jun 13th 10:13 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.41]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I don't think you can buy 10 slot "deluxe sewing kits" from any vendor.&nbsp;&nbsp;From what I gather the these are only in game at all because there was a brief period when the large sewing kits were changed to 10 slot items, but Verant seems to have decided that this was a mistake and now large sewing kits sold by vendors only have the original 8 slots.<br><br>Any of the large sewing kits held by players when they changed the large sewing kits back to 8 slots were converted to the new 10 slot "deluxe sewing kits" during a recent patch to prevent any loss of items from people's inventories when the patch took effect.  So far as I know these are likely to be the only deluxe sewing kits ever available in the game, so if you want one you will need to find another player who has an extra one that he is willing to sell.<br><br>The only 10 slot container you can buy at this time seems to be the deluxe toolboxes sold by the gnomish "pirates" at the igloos in Iceclad.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Shmoozo<br></td></tr>
